# Multi-operator COC merge driver registration (Shard M6 D §5.1).
#
# The forest-ledger artifact lives at:
#   <repo>/.session-notes.shared.md
#   <repo>/workspaces/<name>/.session-notes.shared.md
#
# When two operators concurrently edit the shared ledger and their
# branches merge, the default git text-merge produces conflict markers
# the line-by-line driver cannot resolve correctly (per-row attribution
# is lost; rows reorder unpredictably). The coc-ledger driver parses
# the markdown table by header+separator detection, merges per-row by
# stable ID column, and produces per-row conflict markers naming the
# conflicting owners — preserving attribution that line-merge destroys.
#
# To activate the driver, each operator MUST register it once per clone:
#   git config merge.coc-ledger.name  "COC forest-ledger 3-way merge"
#   git config merge.coc-ledger.driver ".claude/hooks/lib/coc-ledger.js %O %A %B %P"
#
# The .gitattributes entries below bind the file pattern to the driver
# name; the per-clone git-config above binds the name to the command.
# This split is the standard git pattern (attributes are tracked;
# driver commands are clone-local for security — a driver line in
# .gitattributes alone cannot execute arbitrary code on clone).

.session-notes.shared.md merge=coc-ledger
workspaces/*/.session-notes.shared.md merge=coc-ledger
